            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-700 to-teal-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
                Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="border border-green-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="w-full text-left p-6 bg-green-50 hover:bg-green-100 transition-colors duration-200 flex justify-between items-center"
                            aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-pi-content-1" onclick="toggleFAQ(event)">
                        <span class="font-semibold text-lg text-gray-900">What constitutes a personal injury claim in South Africa?</span>
                        <span class="transform transition-transform duration-200 text-green-700">
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                        </span>
                    </button>
                    <div id="faq-pi-content-1" class="hidden p-6 bg-white text-gray-700 border-t border-green-100">
                        <p>A personal injury claim arises when you suffer physical or psychological harm due to the negligence or wrongful act of another party. In South Africa, common examples include injuries from motor vehicle accidents, medical malpractice, slip and fall incidents, and workplace accidents.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border border-green-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="w-full text-left p-6 bg-green-50 hover:bg-green-100 transition-colors duration-200 flex justify-between items-center"
                            aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-pi-content-2" onclick="toggleFAQ(event)">
                        <span class="font-semibold text-lg text-gray-900">How long do I have to lodge a personal injury claim?</span>
                        <span class="transform transition-transform duration-200 text-green-700">
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                        </span>
                    </button>
                    <div id="faq-pi-content-2" class="hidden p-6 bg-white text-gray-700 border-t border-green-100">
                        <p>The time limits (prescription periods) vary significantly. For Road Accident Fund (RAF) claims, if the driver is identified, you generally have 3 years to lodge your claim and 5 years to issue summons. If the driver is unidentified (hit-and-run), you have 2 years to lodge the claim and 5 years to issue summons. For other personal injury claims (e.g., medical negligence, slip-and-fall), the general prescription period is 3 years from the date the cause of action arose. Special rules apply for minors or persons under legal disability. It is crucial to consult with an attorney as soon as possible to ensure your claim is lodged within the strict prescribed period, as missing deadlines can result in your claim lapsing.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border border-green-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="w-full text-left p-6 bg-green-50 hover:bg-green-100 transition-colors duration-200 flex justify-between items-center"
                            aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-pi-content-3" onclick="toggleFAQ(event)">
                        <span class="font-semibold text-lg text-gray-900">What types of damages can I claim in a personal injury case?</span>
                        <span class="transform transition-transform duration-200 text-green-700">
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                        </span>
                    </button>
                    <div id="faq-pi-content-3" class="hidden p-6 bg-white text-gray-700 border-t border-green-100">
                        <p>You can claim for both economic (special) and non-economic (general) damages. Economic damages include past and future medical expenses, past and future loss of earnings, and the cost of future care. Non-economic damages, also known as general damages, compensate for pain and suffering, disfigurement, and loss of amenities of life. In fatal claims, loss of support for dependents and funeral expenses can also be claimed. Note that general damages in RAF claims are subject to a "serious injury" threshold.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border border-green-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="w-full text-left p-6 bg-green-50 hover:bg-green-100 transition-colors duration-200 flex justify-between items-center"
                            aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-pi-content-4" onclick="toggleFAQ(event)">
                        <span class="font-semibold text-lg text-gray-900">What is the Road Accident Fund (RAF)?</span>
                        <span class="transform transition-transform duration-200 text-green-700">
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                        </span>
                    </button>
                    <div id="faq-pi-content-4" class="hidden p-6 bg-white text-gray-700 border-t border-green-100">
                        <p>The Road Accident Fund (RAF) is a state-funded entity in South Africa that provides compensation to victims of motor vehicle accidents who have sustained bodily injuries or to dependents of those who died as a result of such accidents. It covers medical expenses, loss of earnings, and general damages, provided the accident was caused by the negligence of another driver. The RAF operates on a no-fault basis regarding initial payment of medical expenses in certain cases, but compensation for other damages still relies on proving fault.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="border border-green-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="w-full text-left p-6 bg-green-50 hover:bg-green-100 transition-colors duration-200 flex justify-between items-center"
                            aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-pi-content-5" onclick="toggleFAQ(event)">
                        <span class="font-semibold text-lg text-gray-900">Do I need a lawyer for a personal injury claim?</span>
                        <span class="transform transition-transform duration-200 text-green-700">
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                        </span>
                    </button>
                    <div id="faq-pi-content-5" class="hidden p-6 bg-white text-gray-700 border-t border-green-100">
                        <p>While it's not legally mandatory to have a lawyer, it is highly recommended. Personal injury law is complex, involving strict procedures, evidence gathering, expert reports (e.g., medical, actuarial), and negotiation with often well-resourced opposing parties (like the RAF or insurance companies). An experienced personal injury attorney can significantly improve your chances of a successful claim and ensure you receive fair compensation by correctly assessing damages, managing deadlines, and navigating legal complexities.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

